Project: Jagannath University IT Society (JNUITS)
Tech Stack: Next.js 16, Prisma (MongoDB), Tailwind CSS, Shadcn UI, Better Auth.

Guidelines:
1. Data Fetching: 
   - Use Server Components by default.
   - Implement the "use cache" directive (Next.js 16 style) for database queries.
   - Use 'cacheTag' for granular revalidation.
2. Authentication:
   - Use Better Auth for session management.
   - For user data (ID, Name, Image, Email), prioritize the Client-side AuthProvider to avoid redundant server requests.
   - Verify sessions on the server only when security or data mutation is required.
3. Performance & Cost:
   - Minimize Vercel serverless function calls. 
   - Avoid redundant auth.api.getSession() calls if data is already available in props or context.
4. UI/UX:
   - Components must be fully responsive and professional.
   - Use Shadcn UI and Lucide Icons.
5. Coding Style:
   - Always use TypeScript with strict types.
   - Use Server Actions for all data mutations (POST, PATCH, DELETE).